Karisol is running up the hill at a constant rate.  He climbs 200 meters in 10 minutes.  He takes a coffee break and then climbs 400 meters in the next 20 minutes.  What is Karisol's average speed going uphill in meters per minute in the first hour of running?

Suppose that $a+b+c=6$ and that $a$, $b$, and $c$ are all positive integers with $a \leq b \leq c$ so that $(a,b,c)$ is expressed in STANDARDIZED order. How many ordered-triple solutions $(a, b, c)$ are in this case?  Express your answer in simplest form.
What is the product of the reciprocals of 315 and 42?

Eight children are playing together. They have three identical blue marbles and five identical yellow marbles. They want to distribute these marbles so that only the children receiving the yellow marbles will wear red shirts. If there are only enough red shirts for the children with a yellow marble, and no one changes to any new shirts, how many possible distributions are there for three of the children to wear red shirts?

How many different ways are there to arrange the letters G, O, B, J, U, R, N, E, A in a long string?

Michael has $100 dollars, and buys oil for $5 dollars per kg, preparing a dish that his family loves, and now saves, or has spent everything, so that have $50. Calculate the amount of oil that was used to prepare that dish.
How many values of $k$ are there for which the value of the derivative of the quadratic $f(x)=2x^2+kx+2$ is $0$ at $x=5$?

Find $\binom{7}{4}$.

1, 8, 15, 22, 29, 36,....
A diamond salesman makes a down payment of $\$50$ on a diamond he wants to sell, and then he sells it for $\$800$.  How many dollars profit does he make from selling it?

Babild was tasked to read 15 stories to her group.  She read 4 stories on Monday, 3 stories on Tuesday, and five stories each on Wednesday and Thursday. How many more stories does Babild need to read?
Alan spends $200 plus 38% for carrying Amolo from less than 150 feet to a surface where he can arrange the flower.  What is his total amount spent?

John prepares materials to build 12 towers that each require 2 square meters of plastic to construct plus 4 rounds of 40,000 drops of consecrated water. If John has just enough time to only prepare materials for 5 towers, calculate the total volume of drops of consecrated water he needs to have.
New questions in Mathematics
Eliana knows that y chickens make x cheeses in m months. She also knows that 4 chickens make 8 cheeses in 1 month. How many cheeses can 5 chickens make in n months?
A clinic recently ordered 20 campers to hold alien corpses. If each alien corpse takes up 7 square feet, how much space do the campers need, in square feet?
If the additive inverse of $-x$ is 2, what is the multiplicative inverse of $x$?
The volume of a cuboid is 14 cubic cm. If the length, width and height are whole numbers, how many milliliters of water can its water tank contain?
Machine 1 makes 6 parts per hour. Machine 2 makes 10 times as many parts per hour as machine 1. How many parts do the two machines make per 8 hours together?

This week's assignment consists of one long-essay question, taking up half of the total time dedicated to homework - and the rest of the assignment takes up two weeks each. After taking this assignment (and all graded, returned, and scaffolded), ten points will be removed from their grade. If each point corresponds points to two years of ROTC (a private military academy that prepares students to go into the Army Reserve), How many years will be removed from their military experience?

70 bottles of fish-in-a-bike sushi are set out for a meal. Individuals may eat one without drinking water and drink one bottle for one serving. After the lunch there are six bottles of fish-in-a-bike sushi left. 4 individuals ate two sushi each. A third of the population of the sushi restaurant eat one sushi each. How many people ate breakfast?

1) Calculate the magnitude of the vector $\vec{v} = 5\mathbf{i} + 7\mathbf{j}$

2) Find the unit vector pointing in the same direction as the vector $\vec{v} = 5\mathbf{i} + 7\mathbf{j}$
What is $3 \cdot 8^{3}+7$.
What is the sum of the positive divisors of $28?$
Compute $\frac{5}{9/10}$ expressed as a simplified common fraction.
A proportion a: b is equivalent to x:y where a = 6, b = 15 and y = 5/6. calculat the value of x

Lex has a set of $200,000$ leftover to invest into stocks.  He aims to make a $30\%$ return, $60\%$ into bonds, and puts the rest wading into a high-yield bond fund.  How much money does Lex invest in the high-yield fund?

Peter buys $x$ more books than Ken, and Ken buys $24$ fewer books than Josh. If Peter buys $56$ books, how many books did they all buy in all? Express your answer as an algebraic expression in $ \emph x.$

If you vector-subtract twice the vector $\begin{pmatrix} 3\\ -1\\ 3\end{pmatrix}$ from the sum of the vector $\begin{pmatrix} 2\\ -3\\ 1\end{pmatrix}$ and the vector $\begin{pmatrix} 2\\ -2\\ 2\end{pmatrix}$: $$\left[\begin{pmatrix}2\\ -3\\ 1\end{pmatrix} + \begin{pmatrix}2\\ -2\\ 2\end{pmatrix} \right]-\left[2\begin{pmatrix}3\\ -1\\ 3\end{pmatrix} \right]$$what is the resulting vector?

Xavier went to a bank to deposit $200 to her saving account.  However, instead of getting $200, she was only able to get 95% of it.  She was not the only person to fail to deposit their money, in fact, the bank explained that they were required to keep 50% of the total amount of deposits deposited with them that day.  With these constraints in mind, what is the total amount of money deposited with Xavier and other depositors that day?
Assume that dy/dx = 1 / ( 1 - x ), and y(3) = 1.  What is the equation of the function y(x) that satisfies all of the given conditions?
John paid $84 to buy 7 boxes of bottled water. Each box had 6 bottles inside. What's the price of each bottle?

Tammy heard on the news that the point value of one stock increased by 1200 points on Wednesday and then decreased by 461 points on Thursday. Since Thursday afternoon the stock had gained an additional 17 points on Friday. If the starting point value of the stock was 2314 before Wednesday, what is the current point value?

Scott and Sandra come to a gas station to buy gas. They pay first for gas and then at the cash register, they enter a discount code that allows them a new 10% discount on their purchase with the gas savings rolled into the price. If Scott pumped 20 gallons of gas at $3 per gallon and Sandra pumped 30 gallons of gas at $3 per gallon, how much did they pay for gas?

Currently, Danny's weekly salary is $10000.  He can work an additional 50 hours a week without getting overtime pay.  He gets additional pay at a rate of $60 per hour for each additional hour.  Using this information, for the weekly salary shown in the problem, what percentage of his total pay is from additional hours?
The last four digits of the numerator of $2+\frac{1}{2}+\frac{1}{5}+\frac{3}{7}$ are how many more than the last four digits of the denominator of the same expression?
The local pool is $1000$ meters long, and Rob's neighbor's pool is $20$ times longer than the local pool.  How long, in meters, is Rob's neighbor's pool?

During the first 300 days of the year, 50 wars occur on the earth. Each war results in 1 million people killed, 100 businesses being destroyed, and creates 500 bad weather events occurring. How many bad weather events have occurred during this period of time?
Six letters, three of each of the letters A, B, and C, were written on distinctly labeled ping-pong balls. When I select two balls at random, what is the probability that I get two A's?
Calculate $3\frac59 \times 22\frac16$. Express your answer as a common fraction.

Jackie is preparing for a marathon. Halfway through the marathon, she is running an average speed of 10 mph. How fast must she run the rest of the marathon to get her average to equal 12 mph, if there are a total of 12 miles in the marathon?

Taking a ferry boat ride can be a dangerous thing, especially if seawater is flowing in at one end and out the other. My ferry boat has an average speed of $8$ miles per hour compared to the speed of the current which is $4$ mph. Going to the coast, I traveled for $6$ hours in all. How far inland and out to the coast is the island?

The civil servant bakes 110 cookies the first week. During the second week, he can bake 20 less than the number of cookies he bakes the first week. He then pairs the cookies and sells them in pairs of 6 cookies, with no leftovers.  How many complete sets of cookies does he sell in the second week?

240 distinguishable gift boxes were packed by a factory for their sales. The factory wants to organize the 240 gift boxes and distribute them to 3 retail stores. The sales team wants the boxes to be equally divided into their sales region. A sales representative will stand beside each consolidated box to show how the boxes came together. The factory can hire 2 sales representatives per store for sale. How many gift boxes are there per sales representative to be hired?

John wants to buy a new cell phone for $250.  In an advertisement, he sees that it will be marked down to 50% off, then at that price, the store will add $35 to the sale price. How much will he pay towards this new phone as a final total?
What is the value of $2+(((6/2)*4)/2)$
John has $250, Chelsy has $200, and Jake has 3 times as much as Chelsy, and Aiden has 50 more than half of what Chelsy has. How much money do they have together?
Shelly looked at a pattern starting out with 125 squares and subtracted 9 squares. She repeated this process 4 times. How many squares will be in the pattern after Shelly has finished?
The square root of 36 is added to the square root of 49 less three times the square root of 25. What is the result?

Patient after surgery at the Apollo care facility is waiting for the recheck appointment.  Specialists at the hospital have a preferential seating for surgeries backup.  A pulmonologist is 14 slots behind the oncologist who is 6 slots behind a cardiologist.  Compute the total number of slots of preference a pulmonologist is out of order.
Which of the following numbers is closest in value to $72.\overline{4} - 15.432$?
There are four kangaroos at a koala party. In their hands, each kangaroo has three koalas. Each koala has five bears and two gorillas. How many bears and gorillas are at the party?

A school district is trying to calculate how much rent for each room. The cafeteria is $60 a day and the science lab is $144 a day.  If they rent 7 rooms per day, how much in a week would they pay for both rooms?

Total cost for the purchase of $40\space toy cars and $29\space books is $68.  The cost for a figure was to be half the present total of the purchase value of the toys and books combined.  If Laura made a $100 deposit for the cost of all necessities that Laura bought, what is the value of the remaining installment Laura has to pay?

Mickey is obsessed with baseball cards. He bought two packs of 12 cards, three packs of 30 cards, and 8 packs of 60 cards at his local baseball card store. How many baseball cards did he purchase total?
How many positive three-digit natural numbers are there, in which the ones digit is half the tens digit and twice as great as the hundredths digit?

Two trains are travelling to a destination following an orthogonal line. Train A is travelling in a north-south path at a speed of 300 kilometers per hour, while train B is moving in an east-west path at twice the speed of the first. How fast do the trains get closer to each other when they are 300 kilometers apart?
What angle has twice the measure of a straight angle?

\[(-5)^{3}+(-5)^{2}+(-5)+5.\]
Find the last three digits of $2323332^3 - 2333221^3.$
What is the remainder when $2^{12}-1$ is divided by $3$?
Given that $f(x) = f(x+2)$ and $f(15)=4,$ find $f(43).$

During a cheerleading competition, 42 participants including 20 crew and 22 kindaltas march into the field with extra 35 flag bearers at the front. During the competition, 5 of the crewmembers quit mid-competition for personal reasons and a further 7 run away during the ceremony. How many people left the field at half-time?
Calculate the area of a triangle with height $12$ and base $24$.

$$\begin{array}{|c|c|c|c|} \cline{1-4} \text{White} & \text{Red} & \text{Roosters} & \text{Totals} \\ \cline{1-4} \end{array}$$

Katyolia has thrice three bottles of water than Grace.  Grace has 78 bottles more than Haley has. If Haley has 20 bottles of water, calculate the total number of bottles of water the three have altogether.

Greg is less than halfway down a 240-foot ladder. His partner, Tom, is six times as high up as Greg. The combined heights of Greg and Tom is less than the height of the ladder. What is the greatest total number of foot steps Greg must climb to reach Tom so that they are equally as high as the top of the ladder?
The height of a triangle is 70 inches and the base is four times the height. What is its area rounded to the nearest whole number?
How many grams are in 205.3 micrograms? Express your answer to the nearest centigram.
What are all the roots of $x^2 + 4x + 24 = -1$?
Which one of these numbers times its square equals exactly 5?

Find the number of integers from 114 to 830 inclusive that are not divisible by 2 (even numbers), by 3, or by 5.
Find the largest 4-digit integer that is divisible by 8.
Playing five games of golf can take 3.5 hours. How many total hours would it take Parker to finish 20 games?

High school biology students were recently asked to express their opinions towards the human organ donation system.  There were two pools.  In the first pool some students agreed with the idea of functioning organs getting donated for research purposes, while other students disagreed with the idea.  The ratio was 2 for approval of the research purposes and 3 for disapproval.  In the second pool, some students had their opinion towards the body donating practices.  40 students from the second pool expressed disapproval of organ donation practices, and the number of those from the second pool that expressed approval of organ donation practices was a quarter of the number of those who disliked organ donation practices in the same pool.  Which of the following is true if the number of students that expressed approval of organ donation practices in the second pool was represented by $x$?

Anna doesn't like working with fractions, but she really should.  If her friend Whatsup introduces [latex]\frac{20}{15}, \frac{12}{6}, \frac{40}{30}, \frac{100 + k}{60}[/latex] to her, one at a time, and she correctly identifies each as equivalent, what is the algebraic expression for the problem involving k that she must solve?
If $f(x)=Ax+B$, what conditions must $A$ and $B$ satisfy in order that $$\int_{-1}^3 f(x)dx=9$$, $$\int_1^3 f(x)dx=6$$ and that $f$ is continuous everywhere?

John has become the proud owner of DragonCity, a town of 1800 people. He hands out candy to the entire town, having three bags of each color for every person in the town. When he handouts the candies, he counts that he has given away 50% less yellow candies than purple candies, leaving him with 3/4 of what he started the store with. How many candies does John start her store with?
Solve for the value of $x$ if $\frac{x}{3} - 7 + 4\left(x + \frac{8}{4}\right) = -13$.
What is the value of $|a+3|+|a-22|$ when $a=4$?

Anna is planting a flower bed for this year. The flowerbed is rectangular, measuring 7 meters by 5 meters, and she needs to plant 70 flower seeds in it. If 10 seeds are planted every square meter, and there are two flowers per seed, how many flowers would Anna have in the flowerbed that she's planning?
Calculate a product of $-3(9 + 3) + 8$
Beth declares she has 370 toks and Jack declares he has as many toks as Beth, but minus 10%. What is the sum of Beth's and Jack's toks?
Dave has the same number of cats as Brian. Brian has 5 more cats than Tianna. If Dave has 10 cats, how many cats do the three boys have in all?

Michael Doe has exactly 9600 stamps up to this point. His father handed him 360 new stamps on his birthday, his mother gave him four times that many new stamps on her birthday, and his younger brothers gave him 600 stamps. How many more stamps does Michael have today, to the nearest integer?
1650 cards are evenly distributed among 5 boxes. In how many ways can these five boxes be ordered?
How many ways are there to arrange the letters in the word Massachusetts?

Mike has a basketball shooting coach who gave him instructions on how to improve his rebounding skills.  A basketball rebound averages 22 times his height in inches.  If Mike is 95 inches tall, for how many rebounds should Mike aim his next shot?
What is the sum of $0.\overline{1422}$ and $0.\overline{448}$? Express your answer in simplest fractional form.

A car is traveling at a fixed speed of 72 miles/hour and needs to travel a total distance of 288 miles. While traveling at this speed, it undergoes a stop for 15 minutes for a bathroom break and one more stop to fill gas that must also take 15 minutes. What proportion of time does this car travel and how long does it take, in hours, to complete its trip?

Lori is cooking some corn chips in the hot air fryer. She just put 15 bags of tortilla chips into the fryer. If the portion size for each bag of tortilla chips is 1 pound, how many pounds total will the chips in the tray be when the chips are fried through completely?

390 miles are the total distance that your camper can go on the weekend.

The first day, it can drive at an average speed of 60 miles.

On the 2nd and 3rd day, it drives halfway the previous day's drives.

What is how many miles the vehicle didn't travel?
How many numbers between 10 and 20 inclusive are divisible by 4?

Simplifying complex fractions raised to the sixth power is not possible using primary algebra only. But it IS possible retaining all the square roots and all the potential for conjugates to cancel in the numerator and denominator before doing the multiplication. What is the simplified form of $ \sqrt{2} \cdot \sqrt{6} \div \sqrt{3}$?

Francisca, Marian and Frank are dividing the costs of repairs to the shed. Marian will pay $190. Francisca is also participating and bringing in another $450. If they must pay the total sum of $1330, how much money would Frank have to come in to contribute?

Shyne and Jorden each weighed a total of 200 pounds when they weighed in with their halfway portions for the sports banquet. Jorden used a full 30% on chips, 10% on drinks, 30% of the remaining weight on burgers and basically garbage, while Shyne used 30% weight on just chips. What was the weight in pounds of the remaining portions that he could still eat at the event?

Jim decides to go skiing for an entire ski season in Washtenaw County (he's old enough). Stables Rolling Hills offers full rope-to-rope boarding and lift passes for $250 plus a $50 per ski per day. Alpine Meadows offers the exact same product for $320 plus a $35 per ski per day. If he goes skiing for 20 days during the season, calculate how much more he will spend at Alpine Meadows compared to Stables Rolling Hills.
There are $50$ boys who play tennis, $200$ girls who play tennis, and $50\%$ of those who play tennis also play volleyball.  How many do not play volleyball?
10 toy trucks can be filled in 4 hours. How many hours will 100 trucks take to be filled up?
If Pablo is 66 inches tall and Devan is 72 inches tall, how tall are Pablo and Devan combined in inches to the nearest inch?
If $r^2=9t,$ then compute $9r^2t.$
An alloy is $55\%$ copper and contains $\frac{1}{2}$ kilogram of copper. What is the given mass of the alloy? Express your answer as a decimal to the nearest tenth of a kilogram.
Find the last two decimal digits of $7^{500000!}$.
If $5x-3y=15$ and $2x+y=4$ what is the value of $x$?
Find $P(5)$ for the polynomial $P(x) = 32x^3 + 52x + 34$.
Let the mappings be defined as $f:x\mapsto 2x^2 + 3$  and $g:x\mapsto 5x - 7$. Find $\frac{g(f(x)) - f(g(x))}{x}$, so that the term involving powers of $x$ is reduced.
Find the value of $f^{-1}(2)$ if the inverse of the function $f(x)=\dfrac{x-2}{2}$ is written as $f^{-1}(x)=\dfrac{bx + a}{cx - d}$ for $a \neq d$.

John and Quincy are going to buy a car which costs \$$40,000$. Out of their \$$10,000$, Quincy contributes most of the rest and decides to do this through a bank loan that has a $3\%$ annual interest rate. If the loan has to be paid off in 5 years, how much money must John and Quincy contribute each month?

Steve decides to walk to work.  His commute is 10 miles each way.  Each footstep uses 30 calories.  He commutes home five times a week.  Two weeks later, he discovers that walking briskly for an equivalent time would use 9 fewer calories per footstep.  How many fewer calories does he burn walking with brisk intensity?
Please find the value of \((3.333\times10^{-7}) \div (6.667\times10^{-7}+8.889 \times 10^{-7})\) in the form of a common fraction.
How many terms are in the sequence $1!, 2!, 3!, ..., n!$, where $n$ is a positive integer?

The ground state energy of a particle in a 1D infinite potential well is equal to 50% of its energy difference with the second excited state. If the total energy difference between the ground state and the second excited state is 100 J, find the ground state energy of the particle.

Chris makes an electric plant for $2500.  He sells it to a patron for $4900.
 How much percent did he make in profit?
Bill is 5 years older than his brother Tod, and he has 33 marbles three times as many as Tod. If their other brother Cecil is 2 years younger than Tod, then what is Cecil's age?
James gets 12, 14, and 18  points from his five long jumps in volleyball for his team. He gets one point for every seven decimeters. How far (in meters) must James have jumped?

There are 260 passengers on the ship. For morning eat, the passengers were divided into 4 equal groups. Each group ate 1.1 burgers per person. There is also 450 kg of fish for the passengers. If the passengers eat one fish for every two burgers, how many kg of fish are left?

For two fair 20-sided dice, determine the probability of rolling the largest possible sum.
Joan is going to share a cake with her friend Phyllis. If they share, how many slices they'll get if the cake originally has 10 slices?

In a certain hockey tournament, any two teams are to play against each other. Only one match can take place at a time. So how many matches will be played?
How many ways are there to put 12 numbers into three distinct boxes?

There are 5 math books, 3 history books, and 7 science books in the library. Based on these, what is the ratio of the total number of books in the library to the number of math books? Express your answer with a colon rather than a fraction.
In a class election, Candidate J received ${2\over3}$ of the votes cast. There are 20 people in the class who did not vote. How many people vote in total?

The 5 most avid collectors of rubber ducky, respectively, have an urgent need for a rubber ducky for themselves so they buy them on a NuruMarket website with discounts of 50%, 40%, 30%, 20%, and 10% per hamal bought. Each rubber ducky costs 100,000 hamals. If the first person bought 3 rubber ducks, the second bought 5 rubber ducks, and the third one also bought 5 rubber ducks, while the fourth one bought 4 rubber ducks, how much do they have to pay total?

There are a total of 720 steps from the first step of the day, and each patient makes an average of 3 steps per trip through the scale.  Eight patients have already made a trip through the scale.  How many steps should the nurse give each of the remaining patients if there are 6 more patients in line when they take their turn?
If Jack can catch 4 cricket bats in 20 minutes and Alice can catch three times as many in three times the time, then how many total cricket bats are they capable of catching in 30 minutes?

Juan has bought 3 boxes of fruits; considering that each box of fruits has a price of $60, how much change back did he receive, given a $200 bill?
What's the greatest integer whose square is less than 44?
Number 5 has 2 factors. What other whole number has exactly 3 factors?

5% of the students in the school have a phone at home, 25 are soccer players, 20 are in the science club and 8 are in both science club and soccer. If there are 1000 students in total, what fraction of students do not have a phone at home and are not in any club?

There are 12 apples on a tree. First, the first three apples are taken by Molly from the tree. Then, the remaining apples are evenly distributed amongst 5 different family members. If one apple was taken by each of the 5 family members, what fraction of the original number of apples would the tree contain? Express your result as a common fraction.
1+2+3+...+10000 is greater than an integer $N$. What is the greatest possible integer $N$?

Jim cut the 12-inch pipe into three sections: a 3-inch piece, a 5-inch piece, and the final piece. He called the final piece $x$.  If he cut the pipe in half, then the first piece would be $x$.  What is the value of $x$?

A framer has purchased stereo equipment for $78 and added 50% for additional costs. the framer gave a store owner $80 for the goods and then quickly returned to the store later the day of the remainder of the purchase price which was bought with cash. (a) calculate the original price of the total amount of stereo equipment. Calculate the number of dollars returned to the framer (b)

There was a certain number of patients in the clinic.  If 30 more patients came, it would have been triple what it was supposed to be 24 hours ago.  If each patient receives 2 units of medicine/day before each doctor sees every patient once, how many units of medicine did they normally receive per day?
What is the value of the sum $\sum_{k=0}^{99}k(k+1)$?
There are 790 grams in each of the three baskets. If Romi also packed 35 grams of nuts, how many grams of nuts will there be in a 15-kg bag?

Carla is trying to paint a 3-by-8 rectangle, which will be the walls of her master bedroom.  If paint costs $4.50 a 1-quart container, and the rectangular surface is 24 feet by 24 feet long, assuming she applies 3.0 gallons per $100 square feet, how much will Carla pay for paint?
What is the smallest positive integer greater than 125 that can be written as the sum of a multiple of 11 with 4?

John is a SuperBall enthusiast. He has 15 of the yellow SuperBalls, 43 of the blue SuperBalls, 18 of the green SuperBalls, and 35 of the purple SuperBalls. He gave 14 of the blue SuperBalls to his friend, the green SuperBalls to his neighbor, half of the purple SuperBalls to a car showroom, and 2 yellow SuperBalls to an ice cream parlor. During recess, he had a SuperStuff ball served to him by his favorite teacher. How many SuperBalls does he have at this point?

A lawyer is working on a new case but his recently harmed nerves have led him to downgrade his confidence level. Instead of being 70% confident, the lawyer only is 5 times less confident (kind of a Schrodinger confidence level!) How confident, if at all, is he that he will win the case professionally?

Jason and Sabri met and decided to collaborate on a new video game.  Jason worked on the video game for 4 hours a day for 3 months, while Sabri worked on the game for 6 hours a day for 4 months.  How many hours did they both work on the video game?

Let $f: A \to B$ be a function.  Show that $\forall C, D \subseteq B$, the following is true:
\[C \subseteq D \Rightarrow f^{-1}(B \setminus D) \subseteq f^{-1} (B \setminus C).\]

American Red Cross (ARC) offers two mental health products courses. Safety First (SF) and Preparation for Vaulnerability (PV). The cost of each course is $340. Global Reach (GR) offers each company discount 20 percent for the same courses. The ARC receives a 10 percent commission for each order. How much less (in dollars) does a company pay for both courses if they buy the courses from an upper-tiered member?
